Episodes.Title: Taylor's DNA
Episodes.Plot: Taylor is sure she will die of shame when Don and Glenda enter a talent quest for parents at her school. Not one to back away from a challenge, Taylor drags Hector along on a crusade to prove via DNA analysis that Don and Glenda are in fact not her parents, and therefore cannot enter the talent quest.

Episodes.Title: Bigger Than Vegas
Episodes.Plot: Hector secretly nominates Taylor for School Captain, unwittingly igniting her passion for politics. It seems to be a two-horse race as Taylor goes up against the perfect, beautiful and seemingly unbeatable Brittany Flune. Taylor finds herself determined to win, all the while trying to ignore her father's petty annual 'Christmas Lights' rivalry with Brittany's father.

Episodes.Title: Learning to Surf
Episodes.Plot: Taylor is embarrassed when she's sprung fantasising about becoming a pro-surfer, and covers by claiming she can surf. But when heart-throb Leon invites her to enter a surfing competition, Taylor feels she has no choice but to enter. The situation snowballs as Taylor is forced to learn how to surf within a few short days - on her dad's massive Malibu surfboard!

Episodes.Title: Mother In the Nude
Episodes.Plot: Taylor is struck dumb when she arrives home from school with her friends to find her mother creating a nude sculpture of herself. To make matters worse, her class will attend the public unveiling at Sculpture by the Beach but Taylor's effort to upstage the reveal makes a bigger splash than she intended

Episodes.Title: The Chosen One
Episodes.Plot: Taylor is inspired by the teachings of a Buddhist monk, who shares the concept of a simple life without possessions. She decides to live a serene and noble life, and starts by sacrificing all her material possessions in pursuit of true happiness. However, she quickly finds out that this is not as easy as it sounds, as her earthly desires get in the way.

Episodes.Title: The Talk
Episodes.Plot: When Taylor develops a crush on a teenage martial arts instructor, she signs up for classes just to see him. Taylor also avoids her parents from the fear of getting "The Talk".

Episodes.Title: Flag Fall
Episodes.Plot: Taylor becomes image conscious and starts to worry about her appearance, so she adapts to a new sense of style, but Hector isn't very happy with Taylor's new attitude after he agrees to put up the School Flag.

Episodes.Title: The Big Game
Episodes.Plot: After witnessing Leon's soccer skill, and watching him play, Taylor is inspired to join the School Soccer Team.

Episodes.Title: Return of the Mothership
Episodes.Plot: Taylor and Hector spend time with an eccentric elderly couple who believe they will be abucted by aliens and took into outer space in a mothership.

Episodes.Title: The Cross Country
Episodes.Plot: Taylor wins her school cross-country race. But as she basks in her new-found fame and glory, she fails to confess that Mystic Marj drove her to the finish line. Taylor faces the prospect of moving to Scotland when her father inherits a "grand Scottish estate".

Episodes.Title: Taylor Turns Bad
Episodes.Plot: Taylor notices people whispering behind her back, and soon learns that rumours are circulating about her. The discovery gives Taylor a revelation about what it takes to get noticed and sets out to garner the attention she desperately wants.

Episodes.Title: Being Me
Episodes.Plot: With a school dance coming up, Taylor starts to query her image and identity. She fears that her refusal to conform to fashion rules will ruin her social life. To improve her life, Taylor decides to change her name.

Episodes.Title: Leaving Primary
Episodes.Plot: The last day of primary school arrives and it seems that Taylor's circle of friends is being ripped apart, as they all face the prospect of heading off to different high schools. Taylor is torn as she is forced to make some serious decisions about her future.

Episodes.Title: Little Fish
Episodes.Plot: It is Taylor's first day of high school and she smells like rotten fish.

Episodes.Title: Parent-Teacher Night
Episodes.Plot: Taylor is embarrassed by her father's mid-life crisis and tries to prevent others from noticing it when her parents visit school.

Episodes.Title: D.J. Taylor
Episodes.Plot: Taylor's work experience at the local radio station seems to be going well until a humiliating Valentine's Day surprise awaits her.

Episodes.Title: School Trivia Night
Episodes.Plot: Taylor learns that she is not the only one that is embarrassed by her parents when Leon tells her of an embarrassing incident with his parents.

Episodes.Title: Taylor's Self-Portrait
Episodes.Plot: Taylor discovers that a revealing self-portrait is to be auctioned at the school.

Episodes.Title: The Wedding
Episodes.Plot: Taylor finds out that her parents are not officially married, and is even more terrified when she hears of the wedding plans.

Episodes.Title: First Child in Space
Episodes.Plot: Taylor wants to become an astronaut to escape the humiliation of her family.

Episodes.Title: The Family Tree
Episodes.Plot: Taylor is embarrassed to do a project on a member of her family, until she learns she will be visiting her Great Aunt Ally.

Episodes.Title: Divorce Camp
Episodes.Plot: Taylor finds herself lost in the bush when she becomes paranoid that her parents are getting divorced.

Episodes.Title: Taylor Gets a Job
Episodes.Plot: Taylor gets a job as a cat-sitter, hoping to save enough money to buy a cell phone.

Episodes.Title: Rome Wasn't Built in a Day
Episodes.Plot: The night goes terribly wrong when Taylor, Hector and Layla are left home alone.

Episodes.Title: Girl Power
Episodes.Plot: Taylor and Brittany concoct a plan to make sure they remain neighbors.

Episodes.Title: Taylor's Song
Episodes.Plot: After spending a few days with Brittany, Taylor realizes that her family is normal.
